name: Kentel Gumi Temple
address: Jl. Raya Banjarangkan No.4, Tusan, Kec. Banjarangkan, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1:
By tourists, a forgotten precious jewel, as this Hindu temple is, with astonishing buildings. For example one 11-storeys Pagoda and one 9-storeys! But there are also many small buildings with beautiful decorated doors. The temple area is big, perhaps 1.5 football (soccer) fields.
No entrance fee, but please write your name and make your donation in the donation box, by the store to the left of the entrance. I would suggest a minimum donation of 20.000/person (or approx. 2$/person)
review 2: Kentel Gumi Temple is one of 3 temple centre in Bali ( Tri Sad Khayngan Bali ) ,
review 3: Magnificent and well preserved temple. Must put on your spiritual journey list.
review 4: Astonishing Balinese Architecture... Another sacred holy temple in Klungkung Regency...
review 5: Big temple and many shrines inside..  One of the most important temple in Bali
